    "Every optimization technique has weaknesses.",
    "A one-size-fits-all approach cannot adjust to every dataset and accelerate learning to arrive to minima more quickly.",
    "The learning must swiftly converge to the goal with the least amount of loss in the fewest possible repetitions or epochs.",
    "It is important to properly solve the gradient disappearing concern (the gradient is too tiny to adjust the weight in the following loop) [383,384].",
